                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/902: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Buchnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-16T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 16, 1937—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 16—5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>305. Consulate’s 294, September 14, 8 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d704fn39">Not
                        printed.</note> The Council this afternoon passed a resolution<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d704fn40">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                        Journal</hi>, December 1937, p. 907.</note> authorizing the British
                    Government to proceed with a study of the British proposal for the partition of
                    Palestine, it being understood that the British Government would submit a report
                    to the Council and that the Council reserved its position on the substance of
                    the question. Text of resolution will be mailed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
